<article class="article-content">
<p><strong>1v1.LOL</strong> is a third-person shooter that combines fast-paced gunfights with real-time building mechanics. Think Fortnite, but streamlined for quick browser sessions. You drop into an arena, grab weapons, and then it's all about outbuilding and outshooting your opponent. The core loop is addictive: build cover, peek-shot, reposition, repeat.</p>

<p>What sets this game apart is the building system. You can slap down walls, ramps, floors, and cones in real-time — creating your own cover, gaining height advantage, or trapping opponents. Matches typically last 5-10 minutes, making it perfect for quick sessions. The skill ceiling is high though — experienced players can build like maniacs while landing pinpoint headshots. Trust me, your first few matches will be humbling.</p>

<p>The game runs in your browser, no download required, and offers multiple modes: classic 1v1 duels, Battle Royale with up to 23 players, Box Fights for close-quarters combat, and a Just Build mode for pure practice. Whether you're warming up for Fortnite or just want quick competitive action, 1v1.LOL delivers.</p>

<div class="tip-box"><div class="tip-title">📋 Table of Contents</div><ul style="margin: 0.5rem 0 0 0; padding-left: 1.5rem;"><li><a href="#basics">1. Game Basics</a></li><li><a href="#controls">2. Controls</a></li><li><a href="#building">3. Building Mechanics</a></li><li><a href="#weapons">4. Weapons Guide</a></li><li><a href="#tips">5. Tips & Strategies</a></li><li><a href="#faq">6. FAQ</a></li></ul></div>

<h2 id="basics">🎯 Game Basics</h2>

<p>1v1.LOL throws you into a shrinking arena with weapons and building materials. Your goal is simple: be the last player standing. But here's the catch — you're not just shooting, you're building in real-time. Walls for cover, ramps for height, floors for movement, cones for defense. Every structure costs 10 materials, and you cap at 999 per type.</p>

<p>The game has no shields — health starts at 100 and only regenerates with rare med-kit drops. This means every shot matters. Positioning and cover are just as important as aim. The zone shrinks to a 5×5 tile final arena at 3:30, forcing confrontations. You can't turtle forever.</p>

<p>Matches are best-of-7 eliminations. The shrinking zone keeps things moving, and the building mechanics add a strategic layer that pure shooters lack. Master when to box up, when to rush, and when to farm materials — that's what separates winners from losers.</p>

