<div class="tip-box warning"><div class="tip-title">⚠️ Control Tip</div><p style="margin-bottom: 0;">Memorize your build hotkeys (Z, X, C, V) — muscle memory is everything. You should be able to throw up a wall without looking at your keyboard. Practice in Just Build mode until it's second nature.</p></div>

<h2 id="building">🏗️ Building Mechanics</h2>

<p>Building is what makes 1v1.LOL unique. Every structure costs 10 materials, and you passively generate 20 materials per second while alive. Here's what each piece does:</p>

<ul>
<li><strong>Wall:</strong> Vertical cover, blocks shots. Essential for peek-shots and defense.</li>
<li><strong>Floor:</strong> Horizontal platform. Use for height advantage or ceiling over enemies.</li>
<li><strong>Ramp:</strong> Angled surface for vertical movement. Your ticket to high ground.</li>
<li><strong>Cone:</strong> Defensive cap. Traps enemies inside, blocks shots from above.</li>
</ul>

<h3>The "90s" Technique</h3>
<p>This is the bread-and-butter of competitive building. A "90" is a quick vertical stack: place floor + wall + ramp in one fluid motion, then repeat. You rotate 90 degrees each time, climbing straight up while staying protected. Master this and you can outbuild anyone.</p>

<h3>Box Fighting</h3>
<p>Close-quarters combat inside structures. You and your opponent are both boxed up, editing windows to peek-shot. Speed matters here — edit, shoot, reset edit in under a second. The player who edits faster usually wins.</p>

<h3>Editing</h3>
<p>Press G to edit structures. You can open windows, doors, or remove tiles. This is crucial for creating sightlines your opponent doesn't expect. Edit a window, peek-shot, reset the wall — it's the core combat loop.</p>

