<h2 id="weapons">🔫 Weapons Guide</h2>

<p>1v1.LOL has four main weapon slots, each with a specific role. Here's the breakdown:</p>

<table>
<thead><tr><th>Weapon</th><th>Range</th><th>Role</th></tr></thead>
<tbody>
<tr><td>Assault Rifle (AR)</td><td>Mid</td><td>Versatile workhorse, consistent damage, good for pressure</td></tr>
<tr><td>Shotgun</td><td>Close</td><td>Devastating up close, one-shot potential, high risk/reward</td></tr>
<tr><td>Sniper</td><td>Long</td><td>One-shot headshot beyond 50m, punishes overextension</td></tr>
<tr><td>SMG</td><td>Close-Mid</td><td>High fire rate, quick burst damage, melts in box fights</td></tr>
<tr><td>Pickaxe</td><td>Melee</td><td>10 damage, faster material farming, emergency melee</td></tr>
</tbody>
</table>

<p><strong>Loadout Strategy:</strong> AR + Shotgun is the most versatile combo. AR for mid-range pressure, Shotgun for close-range finishes. Sniper users need precision — miss and you're vulnerable during the bolt-action delay. SMG excels in Box Fight mode where everything happens at arm's length.</p>

<h2 id="tips">💎 Tips & Strategies</h2>

<div class="tip-box"><div class="tip-title">🏆 Tip #1: Claim High Ground Early</div><p style="margin-bottom: 0;">Within the first 10 seconds of a match, throw up a double-ramp + wall to gain height. Once elevated, switch to AR and chip 30-40 damage to force your opponent into defensive mode. High ground wins fights — always fight from above when possible.</p></div>

<div class="tip-box"><div class="tip-title">🏆 Tip #2: Master the Peek-Shot</div><p style="margin-bottom: 0;">Never stand still while editing. Edit a window, fire one shot, then reset the wall. The whole sequence should take under 0.5 seconds. This "peek-shot reset" minimizes your exposure while maximizing damage. Practice until it's muscle memory.</p></div>

<div class="tip-box"><div class="tip-title">🏆 Tip #3: Don't Over-Build</div><p style="margin-bottom: 0;">Spamming random walls wastes materials and makes you predictable. A simple 90 is often better than a triple-layer ramp rush. Conserve materials for the final fight — you want at least 200 mats when the zone closes. Smart building beats fast building.</p></div>

<div class="tip-box"><div class="tip-title">🏆 Tip #4: Use the Storm Edge</div><p style="margin-bottom: 0;">In the final circle, hug the moving storm edge instead of running to center. Most players over-peek toward the middle, giving you free side angles. Let them come to you while you stay protected. Positioning wins endgames.</p></div>

<div class="tip-box"><div class="tip-title">🏆 Tip #5: Weapon Switching Is Key</div><p style="margin-bottom: 0;">Don't get attached to one weapon. Fire Shotgun up close, then quick-switch to AR as they retreat. Or use SMG in box fights, then swap to Sniper when they try to escape. Fluid weapon switching catches opponents off-guard and maximizes damage output.</p></div>

<div class="tip-box"><div class="tip-title">🏆 Tip #6: Warm Up in Just Build</div><p style="margin-bottom: 0;">Before jumping into competitive matches, spend 5 minutes in Just Build mode. Practice 90s, box fights, and edit resets. This locks in your muscle memory and gets your hands warm. Pros do this before every session — it makes a noticeable difference.</p></div>

